value: Breeds in North America chiefly from Lake Athabaska and northern Alberta and Saskatchewan southeastward to Manitoba and thence south to North Dakota and Wisconsin. Breeds also in southern British Columbia, Oregon, northern California and Nebraska. Winters in southern United States (chiefly Gulf Coast and Florida) south to Guatemala, the Bahamas and the Greater Antilles.
refer: Peter's Checklist of the Birds of the World

value: Fresh-water marshes, sloughs, bogs, and swamps, usually in forested areas; in winter, primarily on lakes, ponds, slow-moving rivers, and (less frequently) marshes and estuaries.
